<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,618,1219]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1122,1147]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[679,832,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apphia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmanica">
<emphasis box="[679,832,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. burmanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in coloration and in having the ventral margin of the basal lobe of the aedeagus strongly rounded instead of slightly convex. From 
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1436,1159,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Onukia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assamensis">
<emphasis box="[1278,1436,1159,1182]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. assamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[198,350,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apphia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmanica">
<emphasis box="[198,350,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. burmanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in having the basal pair of quadrate processes on the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
